# Frontend Typography and Palette Tokens

- Never hardcode common text sizes or palette colors in new UI code.
- Use tokens from `frontend/src/styles/tokens.css` first.
- Source palette:
  - `#92C7CF`
  - `#AAD7D9`
  - `#FBF9F1`
  - `#E5E1DA`
- Preferred text colors:
  - Primary text: `var(--color-text-primary)`
  - Secondary text: `var(--color-text-secondary)`
  - Gray body/caption text: `var(--color-text-muted)`
  - Very subtle helper text: `var(--color-text-subtle)`
- Preferred UI colors:
  - Primary brand/accent: `var(--color-brand-primary)`
  - Soft brand/accent: `var(--color-brand-soft)`
  - Main background: `var(--color-bg-base)`
  - Card/section surface: `var(--color-bg-surface)`
  - Borders: `var(--color-border-soft)` or `var(--color-border-strong)`
- Preferred sizes:
  - Caption: `var(--font-size-xs)` or `var(--font-size-sm)`
  - Body: `var(--font-size-base)` or `var(--font-size-lg)`
  - Section title: `var(--font-size-xl)` / `var(--font-size-2xl)` / `var(--font-size-3xl)`
- Prefer semantic utility classes when convenient: `.text-title`, `.text-body`, `.text-caption`, `.text-muted`.
- If a new size or tone is truly needed, add a new token in `tokens.css` first, then use it.

## Example

```css
.card-title {
  font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.card-meta {
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.card-surface {
  background: var(--color-bg-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-soft);
}
```
